### Phase 2 — Falcon Threat Graph: Lateral Movement Reconstruction

CrowdStrike Threat Graph visualised the full attack tree across all 3 affected hosts:

```
INITIAL HOST (MFG-WS-031)
  └── svchost.exe [malicious] (PID 4821)
        ├── cmd.exe → ipconfig /all
        ├── cmd.exe → nltest /domain_trusts
        ├── cmd.exe → klist  ← Kerberos ticket enumeration
        └── cmd.exe → mimikatz.exe  ← credential harvesting
              └── [Pass-the-Ticket to MFG-SRV-003]
                    └── svchost.exe [malicious] deployed
                          └── [Pass-the-Ticket to MFG-SRV-007]
                                └── svchost.exe [malicious] deployed
```

**Falcon Custom IOA (Indicator of Attack) rule that would have caught this:**

```yaml
Rule Name:    WMI_Persistence_LowAndSlow
Platform:     Windows
Action:       Detect + Alert

Conditions:
  - event: WmiActivityEvent
  - field: CommandLine
  - operator: contains
  - value: "EventConsumer"
  AND
  - field: ParentProcessName
  - operator: not_in
  - value: ["WmiPrvSE.exe", "svchost.exe"]  # only legit WMI parents
```

> This rule was deployed post-hunt. Had it been active, detection would have occurred on Day 1 of compromise.

