### Phase 3 — Zeek: C2 Beacon Pattern Analysis

Zeek `conn.log` revealed the low-and-slow C2 beacon:

```zeek
# Zeek conn.log entries for MFG-WS-031
ts                  orig_h        resp_h           duration  orig_bytes  resp_bytes
2024-04-01 02:14:01 10.10.8.31   94.102.49.190   0.341s    842         1204
2024-04-01 06:14:03 10.10.8.31   94.102.49.190   0.338s    839         1198
2024-04-01 10:14:01 10.10.8.31   94.102.49.190   0.342s    844         1201
2024-04-01 14:14:02 10.10.8.31   94.102.49.190   0.340s    841         1203
```

**Zeek script to detect low-and-slow beaconing:**

```zeek
global beacon_tracker: table[addr] of vector of time;

event connection_state_remove(c: connection)
  {
  local orig = c$id$orig_h;
  local resp = c$id$resp_h;

  if ( resp == 94.102.49.190 )  # or use threat intel feed
    {
    if ( orig !in beacon_tracker )
      beacon_tracker[orig] = vector();

    beacon_tracker[orig] += c$start_time;

    if ( |beacon_tracker[orig]| >= 4 )
      {
      # Calculate jitter between connections
      local intervals: vector of interval;
      for ( i in beacon_tracker[orig] )
        {
        if ( i > 0 )
          intervals += beacon_tracker[orig][i] - beacon_tracker[orig][i-1];
        }
      # Alert if interval variance < 5 seconds (suspiciously regular)
      NOTICE([$note=C2::Beaconing_Detected,
              $src=orig,
              $msg="Low-and-slow beacon detected — 4hr interval ±2s jitter"]);
      }
    }
  }
```

**Beacon characteristics confirmed:**
```
Interval:     14,400 seconds (exactly 4 hours)
Jitter:       ±2 seconds
Byte size:    840–845 bytes outbound (suspiciously consistent)
Protocol:     HTTPS (443)
Duration:     47 days of undetected beaconing
```

