```

**Key detections:**

```
[CRITICAL] Security event log cleared — 3 hosts
           EventID: 1102 | Hosts: MFG-WS-031, MFG-WS-047, MFG-SRV-003
           Times: within 10 minutes of each other on 2024-03-29
           → Coordinated log clearing — confirms human operator behind keyboard

[HIGH]     Kerberos TGT Request — anomalous account
           EventID: 4768 | Account: svc_mfg_automation
           Source: MFG-WS-031 → used on MFG-SRV-003 (Pass-the-Ticket)

[HIGH]     WMI Remote Execution
           EventID: 4624 LogonType 3 + 4688 WmiPrvSE.exe child process
           → Lateral movement confirmed via WMI remote execution
```

> **Coordinated log clearing across 3 hosts within 10 minutes** is one of the strongest indicators of a human operator actively managing the intrusion — not automated malware. This elevated the threat assessment to APT-level.

